te-2021-mountain-bike-MTB-1-e1613974158439-120x101.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Maxxis-Shorty-mid-spike-mud-tire-update-2021-mountain-bike-MTB-1-e1613974158439-768x648.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Maxxis-Shorty-mid-spike-mud-tire-update-2021-mountain-bike-MTB-1-e1613974158439-696x587.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Maxxis-Shorty-mid-spike-mud-tire-update-2021-mountain-bike-MTB-1-e1613974158439-1068x901.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Maxxis-Shorty-mid-spike-mud-tire-update-2021-mountain-bike-MTB-1-e1613974158439-498x420.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 498w\"></a></p><p>Compared to the original, the Shorty Gen 2 tread pattern gets some notable improvements (thanks to feedback from Maxxis sponsored World Cup DH and EWS riders). The previous “Double Wide” center tread blocks have now been split into two separate knobs. At the shoulders, the cornering knobs are now said to be more supportive and have additional siping for better braking and cornering grip. You’ll also find pairs of little ridges between the knobs which are said to improve mud shedding.</p><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Maxxis-Shorty-mid-spike-mud-tire-update-2021-mountain-bike-MTB-9.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Maxxis-Shorty-mid-spike-mud-tire-update-2021-mountain-bike-MTB-9.jpg\" alt=\"Maxxis Shorty Gen 2 MTB mid-spike mud tire  side profile\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.c