2/Maxxis-Shorty-mid-spike-mud-tire-update-2021-mountain-bike-MTB-9-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Maxxis-Shorty-mid-spike-mud-tire-update-2021-mountain-bike-MTB-9-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Maxxis-Shorty-mid-spike-mud-tire-update-2021-mountain-bike-MTB-9-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Maxxis-Shorty-mid-spike-mud-tire-update-2021-mountain-bike-MTB-9-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Maxxis-Shorty-mid-spike-mud-tire-update-2021-mountain-bike-MTB-9-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Maxxis-Shorty-mid-spike-mud-tire-update-2021-mountain-bike-MTB-9-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><p>Built using their 3C MaxxTerra rubber compound for the EXO casing tires, or 3C MaxxGrip rubber for the DoubleDown or DH casing tires, there’s a Shorty for Trail, Enduro, or DH use (27.5 or 29″ only). All models are Tubeless Ready, and all models are also 2.4″ wide with Wide Trail casings. The reduction in width was done to improve mud clearance in frames with limited clearance to begin with, but it also resulted in a decrease in weight. Smaller tires usually equal less weight, and in this case the DoubleDown and DH tires check in 5% lighter.</p><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Maxxis-Shorty-mid-spike-tire-options-sizing-2021-update-MTB-mud-tire.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Maxxis-Shorty-mid-spike-tire-options-sizing-2021-update-MTB-mud-tire.jpg\" alt=\"Maxxis Shorty Gen 2 MTB mid-spike mud tire size options\" width=\"1234\" height=\"763\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1234px) 1